
===================================
📌 1. Finglish Version (Persian Latin Script)
===================================

📖 **Tashrih:**
    Dastoor `dh_ucf` baraye update ya taghir configuration file-ha (file-haye tanzimat) dar package-haye Debian estefade mishavad. In dastoor motmaen mishavad ke taghirati ke user dade az bein naravad vaghti ke package update mishavad.

⚙️ **Gozine-ha:**
    🔹 `--create-templates` --> 📝 Template file-ha baraye har configuration file misazad.
    🔹 `--no-templates`    --> 🚫 Az template file-ha estefade nemikonad.
    🔹 `--priority=level`  --> 🚦 Tarjih baraye handler-ha tanzim mikonad.
    🔹 `--package`         --> 📦 Package-i ke configuration file-haye aan ra handle mikonad moshakhas mikonad.

🛠 **Mesal-ha:**

    $ dh_ucf --create-templates
    🔹 Template file-ha ra baraye hameye configuration file-ha dar package misazad.

    $ dh_ucf --package mypackage
    🔹  Faghat configuration file-haye `mypackage` ra handle mikonad.

✅ **Mesal sade:**

    $ dh_ucf
    🔹 Be soorate pishfarz, configuration file-ha ra update ya handle mikonad. Agar user configuration file ra taghir dade bashad, `dh_ucf` az user miporsad ke aya taghirat ra hefz konad ya az version jadid estefade konad.

===================================
📌 2. English Version
===================================

📖 **Description:**
    The `dh_ucf` command is used to update or manage configuration files in Debian packages. It ensures that user modifications to configuration files are preserved during package updates.

⚙️ **Options:**
    🔹 `--create-templates` --> 📝 Creates template files for each configuration file.
    🔹 `--no-templates`    --> 🚫 Disables the use of template files.
    🔹 `--priority=level`  --> 🚦 Sets the priority for handler execution.
    🔹 `--package`         --> 📦 Specifies the package whose configuration files are handled.

🛠 **Examples:**

    $ dh_ucf --create-templates
    🔹 Creates template files for all configuration files in the package.

    $ dh_ucf --package mypackage
    🔹 Handles only the configuration files of the `mypackage` package.

✅ **Simple Example:**

    $ dh_ucf
    🔹 By default, updates or manages configuration files. If a user has modified a configuration file, `dh_ucf` will prompt the user to decide whether to keep the changes or use the new version from the package.

